parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
The failure of the oil pump bolt can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Failure and Refusal of Warranty Coverage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealership to properly repair the recalled fuel filter flange and the refusal of Volkswagen to cover the repair costs under warranty can lead to a dangerous situation for the vehicle occupants, as well as financial burdens on the owner.
symptoms: refusal to repair or replace the faulty part
insistence on owner paying for repairs
potential safety risks due to faulty repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become extremely hard to press, leading to a significant loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially in heavy traffic conditions.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes extremely hard to press
the brakes become almost completely unresponsive
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the brake pedal requires excessive force to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A seized rear middle seat belt can prevent the proper use of the seat belt, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear middle seat belt is stuck or seized
unable to be extended or retracted
preventing the passenger from using the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the center drive shaft bearing can cause a high-pitched noise while driving, leading to an uncomfortable ride and potentially causing safety issues if not replaced in time.
